  "text": "The NRAMP family transporters function as general metal ion transporters [CITATION_1] , and we have shown in this study that NtNRAMP1 overexpression in tobacco BY-2 cells suppressed cell cycle arrest and cell death upon excess iron application (Fig. 5) . Plasma membrane localization of NtNRAMP1 (Fig. 6 ) and the decreased rate of iron uptake in the NtNRAMP1 overexpressing cells (Fig. 7B) implies the role of NtNRAMP1 as a modulator of iron uptake or an iron exporter.",
